node.text: @kiacooks credits her mom and grandma for instilling in her a love of good food and cooking, and in today’s episode of Secret Family Recipe, Kia makes one of her grandma’s signature dishes, Chicken & Stuff, with an assist from her mom. Along the way, Kia tweaks things here and there (blanched green beans instead of canned; sautéed chicken instead of boiled) to make the recipe her own while she and her mom talk about the origins of this delicious dish with the whimsical name. Tap the link in our bio for Kia’s family recipe. #thekitchn

node.title: Secret Family Recipe: Chicken & Stuff with @kiacooks

node.text: When @andreuhhhhhh and @dcjerbear first bought their 100-year-old “fixer upper” in 2018, they felt a little delusional. “It was a disaster when we first toured it, but somehow we both were able to see past the clutter to the potential that laid below the surface,” Andrea says. After spending 18 months giving the entire house a loving and painstaking (mostly DIY) renovation, we think the finished project could not be more perfect. Tap the link in our bio for Andrea’s Renovation Diary — we’re sharing before & after photos, and where every single dollar of their budget went. (Image: @thejenchase) #thekitchn
